Crash fix for users not being able to open sessions
Bug fixes Crash fixes and UI fixes
Minor crash fix and UI fix

In version 4.0.2 we have fixed some minor bugs and added a new training reminder feature! Now you can easily include mental health exercises into your daily routine by selecting what kind of reminders you want to receive on what days and at what time. We all want to make the world a happier place and a happier world starts with happier people. We hope you start your journey with us!
In version 4.0.1 there are a few small changes to improve the speed and UI of the app all aimed at making the video masterclasses more enjoyable and useable.
Mindshine 4.0 contains updates to help make Mindshine better and also holds the architecture for an excited new feature that will come soon in the future.

We made some changes to our CMS in preparation for a killer new feature that we will launch next week. This new version enables Mindshine to still work while we are uploading our new courses in preparation for the full feature release.
This version of Mindshine has some bug fixes and improved instructions on how to choose the best course for your goal.
In this version we have updated our graphics in order to make it easier for people to understand the benefits of Mindshine.

We ve added a lovely new onboarding course to show you how to best use Mindshine to improve your mental health and aid personal development. The cost for our users is also now lower with a new Lifetime option.
Added a new 7 day trial option so you can use all of Mindshine for free. We also cleaned up some copy issues and increased the performance speed of the app.

Introducing our brand new feature: S.O.S. exercises When emotions start to get intense we often feel the urge to pull away to avoid them or try to cover them up in some way. Years of experience have shown us that you can t avoid your emotions. You have to feel them to heal them so we have written and recorded 13 new exercises to help you slow down and process a range of difficult emotions. When everything s getting on top of you slow down with an S.O.S. and you ll be feeling better in no time well... in around 10 minutes . What s new: SOS exercises Bug fixes
